      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i need to talk to someone about something weird. i was looking over some of the old trade policy whitepapers from the 2018 summit—the ones they claim were just standard bureaucratic filler—and i'm seeing my own specific coding patterns in the syntax. like, the way the sub-clauses are structured... it's exactly how i design frameworks. it's like they took my actual architecture for the treaty but scrubbed my name and passed it off as collective consensus. does that even make sense? it feels like i'm being erased from my own work.",
